Key Focus Areas of Budget 2024-25
Infrastructure & Growth:

Capital expenditure increased to ₹11.11 lakh crore (3.4% of GDP).

Expansion of PM Gati Shakti for multimodal connectivity.

Agriculture & Rural Development:

PM-KISAN direct cash transfers retained at ₹6,000/year for farmers.

Focus on Nano DAP fertilizers and tech-driven farming.

Green Energy:

Viability gap funding for offshore wind energy.

Mandatory biomass blending in coal power plants.

Tax Reforms:

No changes to income tax slabs (interim budget).

Extended tax benefits for startups and sovereign funds.

Healthcare & Education:

Ayushman Bharat coverage expanded to ASHA workers.

New IITs, IIMs, and medical colleges announced.
